description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;We are seeking experienced and motivated Clerical Officer in Ophthalmology to join the Portsmouth Staff Bank based at Portsmouth University Hospital.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;Required Skills &amp; Experience:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Education to GCSE Level, grade C or above&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Previous experience of providing clerical support in a busy and challenging environment&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Evidence of experience of working with the public&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Computer literacy &amp; keyboard skills&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Literacy and numeracy&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;DESIRABLE&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience of working in a healthcare environment&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Good office skills&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Knowledge of hospital databases/ information systems (PAS)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Knowledge of Microsoft Office&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This position is for 37.5 hours per week, Monday to Friday with the occasional Saturday morning. &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Our Bank workers are invaluable to us and in return of your hard work and commitment we can offer the following benefits:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Competitive pay rates – enhanced payrates paid during the weekend and Bank Holidays&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Flexible working pattern&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Opportunities to work across sites, gaining invaluable knowledge and experience&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Priority placements over an Agency Workers&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A dedicated onsite bookings team&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Electronic timesheet submission and weekly pay&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;An onsite office and designated Business Partners to offer daily support&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A professional compliance team that will ensure you remain compliant to work&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;We also offer Core Skills Training&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Please apply directly to this advertisement, ensuring you upload a full and up to date CV. Successful applicants will be contacted shortly. If you require further information then please contact the Portsmouth Staff Bank Recruitment Team on 0333 577 3316.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
